<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-08-24T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-08-24T22:00:00-05:00" n="162" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d162">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.20 Defense/37<hi rend="superscript">9/17</hi>: Telegram</note>
                                <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Sparks</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss></hi></head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-08-24T22:00:00-05:00">August 24, 1940—10 p.m. [<hi rend="italic">a.m.?</hi>]</date><lb/>[Received 12:11 p.m.]</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>134. From Colonel Harris to Colonel Ridgway. Haitian Government
                                    authorizes army plane to photograph airfields, ports, and
                                    harbors. May arrive any time. Will be based at
                                        Port-au-Prince.<note n="78" xml:id="d162fn1">Despatches No.
                                        971, August 26, 1940, No. 972, August 27, 1940, and No. 973,
                                        August 27, 1940, report the successful conclusion of the
                                        army and navy staff talks with the Government of Haiti
                                        (810.20 Defense/37<hi rend="superscript">11/17</hi>, 37<hi rend="superscript">12/17</hi>. and 37<hi rend="superscript">13/17</hi>).</note></p>
                                <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Sparks</hi></signed></closer>
                            </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>